                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2377: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-01-10T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 10, 1922—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Your no. 8 of January 7, 11 a.m. See the Minister for Foreign Affairs, … talk
                    with him along the lines indicated in our instructions of December 24, 1921, 3
                    p.m., and lay before him the plan outlined in that telegram. Present the plan
                    merely as a suggestion, however, so as to avoid the possibility that he will
                    immediately unconditionally reject it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
